It would be awesome to be able to chain when using any of the Atom API's. Right now, I have to say 

```
cursor.setBufferPosition(newPosition);
if (cursor.isInsideWord()) {
  // exec. stuff here
}
```

I noticed most of the rest of the Cursor API isn't fluent, and seems to be the case with other API's. Is there any objection to a chainable API?
